input.command:
ghx run pr.reviews.submit --input - <<'EOF'
{
  "owner": "aryeko",
  "name": "ghx-bench-fixtures",
  "prNumber": 444,
  "event": "REQUEST_CHANGES",
  "body": "run_1772555729706\n\nThanks for the update. I found a few blocking issues that need to be fixed before this can merge:\n- `src/utils/helpers.ts` has a syntax error in the import statement (`improt`), which will fail TypeScript compilation.\n- `divide(a, b)` currently ignores `b` and always divides by zero, so it returns incorrect results and can produce `Infinity`.\n- `waitForReady()` uses an unbounded busy loop, which will peg the CPU and never return; this should be replaced with a bounded/asynchronous waiting strategy (or removed).\n\nPlease address these and I can re-review quickly.",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 2,
      "body": "Typo in the import keyword: `improt` should be `import`. As written, this file will not parse and the build/typecheck will fail."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 9,
      "body": "`divide(a, b)` currently returns `a / 0`, which ignores the `b` parameter and always divides by zero. This is a functional bug. Please use `a / b` and decide how you want to handle `b === 0` (throw, return `null`, etc.) consistently with project conventions."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/utils/helpers.ts",
      "line": 13,
      "body": "This `while (true)` loop is an infinite busy-wait and will consume CPU indefinitely while blocking progress. Please replace with a non-blocking wait mechanism (event/callback/promise polling with delay and timeout) so the function can terminate safely."
    }
  ]
}
EOF

